For Linux systems (tested on Ubuntu 18.04)
Pre-installed programs required:
1.espeak
2.translate-shell (from https://www.soimort.org/translate-shell/trans)
3.tor
4.torsocks
5.anki

USING
1. Compile the source code and copy the file runscript.sh to build/classes/java/main/ folder,
grant the file execution rights for this script.
In this file you can adjust the translation direction.
2. Then copy needed english words or entire english text to the file input.txt
3. Run script runscript.sh
4. Your translated words for import to Anki will be in the file wordswithtranslation.txt
5. Run Anki, choose file-import, then our file wordswithtranslation.txt, then choose separator \ ,
tick the "html tags" and press OK.

EXAMPLE OF FILE FORMAT for input.txt

#  >face journey>емоційний вираз обличчя   you put here english and translated words, divided by ">" at the beginning
of the line and between english word or english phrase and your translation.
#  "get the runaround" translating the entire phrase from Google, the words framed in quotes
#  не ставити апостроф у англійській частині, крапку

>merge>з'єднати
>dizzy>запаморочливий
>apt>схильний
"get the runaround"
here can be text too
>biting>кусаючий
>disgraceful>ганебний
>stiffly>жорстко
